value.name: Musée Saint-Raymond | Toulouse Tourisme
value.snippet: Le musée Saint-Raymond possède une des plus belles collections de sculptures romaines de France. Près de 1000 pièces évoquent le cadre de vie des Celtes et des Romains dans la région toulousaine. Un musée qui ne vous laissera pas de marbre ;) Tolosa, 2 000 ans d'histoire

value.name: Musée Saint-Raymond | Tourismus in Toulouse
value.snippet: Das Musée Saint-Raymond befindet sich in einem ehemaligen Kollegium aus dem 16. Jahrhundert. In ihm ist eine umfangreiche archäologische Sammlung mit über 1000 Exponaten untergebracht, die den Alltag der Kelten und Römer in der Region Toulouse nachzeichnen.

value.name: The Musée Saint-Raymond | Tourism in Toulouse
value.snippet: The Musée Saint-Raymond boasts one of the most beautiful collections of Roman sculptures in France. Nearly 1000 pieces recall the way of life of the Celts and the Romans in the area surrounding Toulouse. A museum of marble sculptures that won’t leave you cold. Tolosa; 2000 years of history

value.name: Musée Saint-Raymond (Toulouse, Frankrig) - anmeldelser - Tripadvisor
value.snippet: Toulouses arkæologiske museum, Saint-Raymond, har siden 1891 haft til huse i en bygning fra 1500-tallet, et tidligere universitetskollegium, lige ved siden af Basilique Saint-Sernin. Bygningen er konstrueret oven på en kirkegård med tidlige kristne grave fra 300-tallet, som man kan se i museets kælder.

value.name: Musée Saint-Raymond - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Musée Saint-Raymond (in English, Saint-Raymond museum) is the archeological museum of Toulouse, opened in 1892. The site originally was a necropolis , and in later constructions was a hospital for the poor and pilgrims, prison, student residence, stables, barracks and presbytery, eventually becoming a museum in 1891.

value.name: Musée Saint-Raymond (Toulouse) - All You Need to Know BEFORE You Go
value.snippet: The museum Saint-Raymond, preserves and enhances an archaeological site that is among the largest in France.Push its doors to discover the Roman town of Tolosa, the sculptures of the villa Chiragan, the remains of a necropolis from late antiquity. value.name: SAINT-RAYMOND MUSEUM, TOULOUSE ARCHAEOLOGY MUSEUM | TOULOUSE | Museum
value.snippet: At the Saint-Raymond Museum, the Archaeology Museum of Toulouse, you enter a place that will not leave you indifferent. On the 2nd floor, the objects presented and the models remind you of Toulouse and its region at the time of the Gauls and the Romans.
